The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has in­augurated five loan schemes for 138 rural farmers in Imo. Mallam Abubakar Nuhu-Fikpo- Director-Gen­eral of the Establishment while inaugurating the schemes in Owerri, on Tues­day, explained that the pro­grammes, organized by the Directorate’s Department of Rural Employment Promo­tion (REP), were targeted at alleviating the problems of unemployed Nigerians living in rural areas. Nuhu-Fikpo, who was rep­resented by the Directorate’s Co-ordinator in Imo, Mrs Ngozi Ihenacho, said that 100 persons would benefit from the sustainable Agricultur­al Development Training Scheme, with each benefi­ciary receiving an empower­ment loan of N100,000. He listed the other schemes to include the Ag­ricultural Enhancement Scheme for 15 beneficiaries and the Sustainable Agricul­tural Development Empow­erment Scheme, for 12 bene­ficiaries.